<subSubSection id="894E9904CB9AD2BCED4DABECD26F36B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F2C4E54B2BD32EDD62BFCB6B3A3D93F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E1409367F68BA2BCCFCF79DA342C5447" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to the Temascaltepec region of Mexico State at around 1200 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="407E6F4F0AF72A4A880843C68236C182" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="CD3691D3C38D841E2D34DD310F933C9B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. Est. 
<normalizedToken id="F7804C056DCE0AFB2A749768504CC921" originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Temascaltepec, 
<emphasis id="524CACAFDF707B9E446CC26D9708B0DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G.B. Hinton et al</emphasis>
. 8258 (F, K, MO); ibid., Yperricones, 
<emphasis id="9404016CC7F1343E07507AE0B7C301FD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G.B. Hinton et al</emphasis>
. 341 (K); ibid., Pungarancho, 
<emphasis id="9B569AF8E94F959BDC3D71C429839E19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G.B. Hinton et al</emphasis>
